data.title: Meijer Partners with HP on Digital Photo Centers and Online Printing
data.meta_description: Meijer has partnered with Hewlett-Packard, Palo Alto, Calif., as the retailer launches a complete digital end-to-end HP Photo Center solution.
data.text:
GRAND RAPIDS, Mich. — Meijer has partnered with Hewlett-Packard, Palo Alto, Calif., as the retailer launches a complete digital end-to-end HP Photo Center solution. In addition, Snapfish by HP will host Meijer’s online photo site, which will include the capability to have online orders for prints and creative photo products mailed directly to a customer’s home or sent to a Meijer location for fast, high-quality printing and convenient in-store pick up. HP simultaneously launched a $300 million global marketing campaign called “What do you have to say?” that enables users to combine their content with free, exclusive content from singer and fashion designer Gwen Stefani, Burton Snowboards founder Jack Burton and graphic designer Paula Scher.
